Index0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThinkers and Dreamers honours Carl C. Berger, professor of Canadian history at the University of Toronto for more than forty years and author of influential works on Canadian intellectual history. In this collection, Professor Berger's colleagues and former students explore the currents of intellectual life in North America since the mid-nineteenth century.Broad in scope, the essays range in content from a commentary on works in intellectual history to analyses of the development of particular disciplines and distinctive cultural institutions. Several of the contributions provide sharp critiques of historical thought, including a discussion of professional scholarship and an analysis of the field of intellectual history. Others address issues that combine institutional and cultural history, such as an examination of Victorian Canada and a discussion of immigration and citizenship. These varied reflections aptly convey Berger's contributions to the study of Canadian history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aFriesen, Gerald, eeditor.1 aOwram, Doug, eeditor.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUTP eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2015z978311066769108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311049095440uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/9781442690165423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442690165.jpg  a978-3-11-049095-4  University of Toronto Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066769-1  UTP eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSH